               <p>JOHN ANDREWS. I am a <rs id="t18310630-247-viclabel1299" type="occupation">master chimney-sweeper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-247-victim1805 t18310630-247-viclabel1299"></join>, and keep my soot in a cellar, in <placeName id="t18310630-247-crimeloc1300">Horace-street, Edware-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-247-crimeloc1300" type="placeName" value="Horace-street, Edware-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-247-crimeloc1300" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-247-off1297 t18310630-247-crimeloc1300"></join>; the prisoner was a <rs id="t18310630-247-deflabel1301" type="occupation">sweep</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-247-defend1804 t18310630-247-deflabel1301"></join> on his own account - he lodged at my house, and I bought soot of him, but he does not buy mine. I missed soot three or four times, and told McDonal to watch.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-247-person1806">
                  DAVID 
                  McDONAL
               <interp inst="t18310630-247-person1806" type="surname" value="McDONAL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-247-person1806" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-247-person1806" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I let the cellar to the prosecutor. On the 3rd of June, about half-past five o'clock in the morning, the prisoner came into the cellar with an empty sack, and went out with a full one - I stood in the street, but as he worked for Andrews I took no notice of his going in, and as he brought a full sack out I followed him - he took it into Crawford-street; there was nothing but the prosecutor's soot in the cellar.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. He says it was half-past five o'clock; I can prove I was drinking with a man from a quarter to five till eleven. Witness. As near as I can guess it was halfpast five - I spoke to him; and about ten minutes before six o'clock he was setting on a public-house bench, in Crawford-street; I knew him very well before - it was Friday morning, the 3rd of June.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-247-person1807">
                  JOHN 
                  ANDREWS
               <interp inst="t18310630-247-person1807" type="surname" value="ANDREWS"></interp>
